title: What is CS0101?
labels: All compiler errors have to be fixed

sections.title: Symptoms
content: • You are seeing the following error in the console window:
error CS0101: The namespace `__' already contains a definition for `__'

sections.title: Cause
content: CS0101 is caused when a namespace has duplicated identifiers. The example below has the same identifiers for both methods.
error CS0101: The namespace `ExampleNamespace' already contains a definition for `Method'

sections.title: Resolution
content: In order to fix the CS0101, you will need to ensure that each identifier in your namespace is unique. Please see how we have fixed the example below:
This error can also be fixed by ensuring that all classes have a unique identifier. It is common to have duplicate scripts in a project.
